    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-01T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="93"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1404</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi>
                        </placeName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d93fn2">For papers concerning the American
                            Minister’s withdrawal from Belgium, see <ref
                                target="frus1917Supp01v01#pg_628">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, Supplement 1, pp.
                                628</ref>
                            <hi rend="italic">et seq.</hi>
                        </note>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-01T12:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1918, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.05 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to <persName corresp="#p_HCGFv1">Hertling</persName>’s speech the
                    Belgian Government declares that its thought has not changed since the response
                    it made to the Pope. It will discuss peace only in concert with its allies.
                        <persName corresp="#p_HP1">Hymans</persName> makes statement to this effect
                    to-day.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
